latestIgtvVideos.title: Night time skincare routine!!!✨
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Products used:
1.@thebodyshopindia @thebodyshop Camomile makeup remover( skip this step if u have not applied any makeup)
2. @thebodyshopindia drops of youth gentle foaming wash ( I actually keep changing face washes tbh that’s because i like trying new ones!! But i must say i love this brand)
3. @glamglow flashmud brightening treatment (please note: i apply mask only once or twice in a week) 
4. @pixibeauty glow tonic
< I usually use serum after this .. which i somehow forgot to film it > 
5. @lorealparis @lorealindia Revitalift essence( i have recently started using this one .. yet to see results !!)
6. @thebodyshopindia drops of youth bouncy eye mask
7. @cetaphilme @cetaphil_india moisturizing cream ( i always prefer using this during night time rather than day time )
8. @palmers @palmersindia skin therapy oil( always make sure to use facial oils only during night time ) 
9. @laneigeindia @laneige_us lip sleeping mask!! ( can’t really say how much i love this one! ) 
These are what I’m currently using . (Excluding emulsion, chemical exfoliators, sheet masks) •••••••••••••••••••••••••
Also please note: all products work differently on each person depending on their skin . So please research about what suits the best to your skin. •••••••••••••••••••••••••

latestPosts.caption:
August has been a whirlwind of new beginnings and memorable moments.✨

From celebrating my birthday 🎂to the excitement of buying a new car 🚘 , this month started with joy.

Traveling to Dubai ✈️ added adventure to the mix, while new brand collaborations 🤝 fueled my passion.

I discovered a new love for matcha 🍵 and embraced solo dates, cherishing my own company.

Of course, there were a few bumps along the way—failures that I now see as valuable lessons.

Coping with personal challenges wasn’t easy, but it all led to a sense of growth 🌱.

I ended this month with a peaceful puja at home 🪔 , feeling grounded and grateful.

August, you’ve been filled with everything new and good, and I’m ready to take on what comes next ✨
